1
00:00:06,757 --> 00:00:08,509
-This the place?
-This the place.

2
00:00:12,971 --> 00:00:14,598
-This the stuff?
-This the stuff.

3
00:00:14,681 --> 00:00:16,642
And this is no ordinary stuff, Morty.

4
00:00:16,725 --> 00:00:18,602
This sap is primo.

5
00:00:25,859 --> 00:00:27,945
-What the hell?
-Shit! Vines!

6
00:00:29,530 --> 00:00:33,283
Locusts come to harvest my bounty.

7
00:00:33,367 --> 00:00:35,244
Hey, giant ancient tree guy.

8
00:00:35,327 --> 00:00:37,829
Sorry. We thought the sap
was accountability-free.

9
00:00:37,913 --> 00:00:40,499
Yeah, we're not locusts,
just a couple adventurers.

10
00:00:40,582 --> 00:00:43,001
Spacefarers.

11
00:00:43,085 --> 00:00:45,212
You consume your planets,

12
00:00:45,295 --> 00:00:48,715
then spread your sickness
to the stars.

13
00:00:48,799 --> 00:00:51,051
Nah. Nah, man.
We're clean, I promise.

14
00:00:51,134 --> 00:00:54,012
Yeah, yeah. We just got tested,
and I got a bit of a soy allergy.

15
00:00:54,096 --> 00:00:58,141
I have a place for animals like you.

16
00:00:58,225 --> 00:01:02,187
You will be reformed!

17
00:01:04,855 --> 00:01:06,066
What is...

18
00:01:24,042 --> 00:01:25,544
...this?!

19
00:01:25,627 --> 00:01:27,588
Yeah, Morty. Not ideal.

20
00:01:27,670 --> 00:01:29,798
But I promise you,
the sap will be worth it.

21
00:01:29,881 --> 00:01:32,551
I had the craziest night
on this stuff a few weeks ago.

22
00:02:04,458 --> 00:02:06,918
I'm all wobbly, Rick.
What the fuck's going on?

23
00:02:07,002 --> 00:02:08,419
I'm in the same position you are.

24
00:02:08,502 --> 00:02:11,173
But I can guess that those roots
extracted the biological data

25
00:02:11,256 --> 00:02:13,967
we think of as our minds
and reincarnated us as amoeba.

26
00:02:14,051 --> 00:02:15,719
How do we get our old bodies back?

27
00:02:15,802 --> 00:02:17,262
Well, that's the wrong question,

28
00:02:17,346 --> 00:02:19,431
but it's the one
all new cellmates ask.

29
00:02:20,349 --> 00:02:21,600
"Cellmates."

30
00:02:21,683 --> 00:02:23,810
We use humor to stay sane
in this place.

31
00:02:23,894 --> 00:02:26,438
Yes, sir. Many folks have tried
to raid this planet

32
00:02:26,521 --> 00:02:27,939
and ended up down here.

33
00:02:28,023 --> 00:02:30,692
Growth and rebirth.
The ball and chain around our ankles.

34
00:02:30,776 --> 00:02:33,028
In here, a man can truly change.

35
00:02:33,111 --> 00:02:35,238
But don't mistake that for freedom.

36
00:02:35,322 --> 00:02:38,158
Give me your cytoplasm,
you limp-dick motherfucker!

37
00:02:47,084 --> 00:02:48,168
-What?
-Huh.

38
00:02:48,251 --> 00:02:49,753
Guess if you die, you start over.

39
00:02:49,836 --> 00:02:51,463
Good thing we hadn't made
much progress.

40
00:02:51,546 --> 00:02:54,091
-Try not to die, Morty.
-Hello, my delicious friends.

41
00:02:54,174 --> 00:02:56,593
-He's multicellular now!
-Back for another helping?

42
00:02:56,677 --> 00:02:59,388
-Spawn-camping piece of shit!
-Jesus!

43
00:02:59,471 --> 00:03:01,515
Prison rules, Morty.
Get to the top of the food chain

44
00:03:01,598 --> 00:03:02,891
or you're someone's dinner.

45
00:03:03,850 --> 00:03:05,686
Hey, get in here.
We need the nutrients.

46
00:03:06,478 --> 00:03:08,689
Oh, it's like salty tapioca.

47
00:03:08,772 --> 00:03:11,358
If this place is dumb enough
to let us manipulate our DNA, Morty,

48
00:03:11,441 --> 00:03:12,984
then we'll just evolve our way out.

49
00:03:13,068 --> 00:03:14,069
First step is fins.

50
00:03:14,152 --> 00:03:16,238
-Wait. How?
-Mitosis, Morty.

51
00:03:16,321 --> 00:03:18,365
Think really hard
about being your own daughter.

52
00:03:26,790 --> 00:03:29,334
Being a fish isn't so bad.
Swimming is fun.

53
00:03:29,418 --> 00:03:30,877
I do like how you're never thirsty.

54
00:03:30,961 --> 00:03:32,671
And the whole world's your toilet.

55
00:03:39,177 --> 00:03:41,596
Oh. Oh, air. So good.

56
00:03:41,680 --> 00:03:42,848
So good.

57
00:03:52,983 --> 00:03:53,984
Toughen up, Morty.

58
00:03:54,067 --> 00:03:55,736
The primordial soup
was just the beginning.

59
00:03:55,819 --> 00:03:57,446
We're in some kind of hollow earth.

60
00:03:57,529 --> 00:03:59,322
The reincarnation field
must be contained

61
00:03:59,406 --> 00:04:00,741
within the warden's root lattice.

62
00:04:00,824 --> 00:04:03,243
If we escape to the surface,
we escape the cycle.

63
00:04:05,829 --> 00:04:08,290
Goddamn it, Morty. You're a lungfish.

64
00:04:08,373 --> 00:04:09,374
Use your lungs.

65
00:04:26,349 --> 00:04:28,018
-Sorry.
-You know how much willpower it takes

66
00:04:28,101 --> 00:04:29,311
to drown yourself?

67
00:04:29,394 --> 00:04:30,687
What do you want to try next?

68
00:04:30,771 --> 00:04:32,814
I got eight words for you...

69
00:04:32,898 --> 00:04:33,940
legs.

70
00:04:34,983 --> 00:04:37,903
This is great. We let our food
come to us and plan our next move.

71
00:04:37,986 --> 00:04:39,988
I think I'm stuck.

72
00:04:40,071 --> 00:04:41,531
-In our own web?
-It's fine.

73
00:04:41,615 --> 00:04:43,450
I'll use you and pull myself up.

74
00:04:43,533 --> 00:04:45,034
Don't! Damn it!

75
00:04:47,120 --> 00:04:48,830
Not so fun, is it?

76
00:04:48,914 --> 00:04:50,540
-Eat shit!
-I'm gonna!

77
00:04:50,624 --> 00:04:53,835
Morty, I'm gonna evolve wings,
and then I'm gonna kill that guy.

78
00:04:57,339 --> 00:04:58,965
This is amazing, Rick.

79
00:04:59,049 --> 00:05:00,467
And really quick to get to.

80
00:05:00,550 --> 00:05:02,636
Birds are basically small dinosaurs.

81
00:05:03,220 --> 00:05:04,930
All right, Morty,
there's no thermals,

82
00:05:05,013 --> 00:05:07,557
so we've got to evolve really
specific wings to get up there.

83
00:05:07,641 --> 00:05:09,518
Oh, you can't build us
mech suits yet?

84
00:05:09,601 --> 00:05:11,269
Nah. Birds can get
wherever they want,

85
00:05:11,353 --> 00:05:13,104
but can't do anything
once they get there.

86
00:05:13,188 --> 00:05:14,773
It's like astral projection.

87
00:05:14,856 --> 00:05:16,983
Oh, shit! He can get us
down here too.

88
00:05:23,281 --> 00:05:25,367
All right. Pretty obvious
we gotta climb a tech tree

89
00:05:25,450 --> 00:05:26,868
to climb the actual tree.

90
00:05:26,952 --> 00:05:28,411
And we do that with...

91
00:05:28,495 --> 00:05:31,748
Hands. Supple, grippy hands

92
00:05:31,832 --> 00:05:33,750
and a pretty familiar version of--

93
00:05:33,834 --> 00:05:35,627
-God, just go already.
-Don't wait up!

94
00:05:42,551 --> 00:05:44,928
This watering hole is pretty tense.

95
00:05:45,011 --> 00:05:48,014
-Pretty ape-heavy.
-Exactly.

96
00:05:48,098 --> 00:05:51,183
This hole's for apes only. Clear out.

97
00:05:51,268 --> 00:05:53,728
Oh, we were just drinking water.

98
00:05:53,812 --> 00:05:55,438
And using tools!

99
00:05:55,522 --> 00:05:58,692
Hey, look, this guy's
jerking off a stick with his rock.

100
00:05:58,775 --> 00:06:00,652
He’s a stick stroker!

101
00:06:00,735 --> 00:06:02,320
I'm gonna end you, tool man.

102
00:06:02,404 --> 00:06:04,489
We can move along.

103
00:06:07,158 --> 00:06:08,869
-Oh my God, Rick!
-Hey, what the fuck?

104
00:06:08,952 --> 00:06:11,204
Hey! Kill those monkeys
slightly different than us.

105
00:06:11,288 --> 00:06:13,540
-What are you doing, Rick?
-They started it.

106
00:06:13,623 --> 00:06:16,418
Domination through technology, Morty.
We're going apex.

107
00:06:16,501 --> 00:06:17,919
This stick is your god!

108
00:06:18,003 --> 00:06:19,462
He's got a thing!

109
00:06:21,756 --> 00:06:22,757
Rick?

110
00:06:22,841 --> 00:06:24,092
I'm doing this for both of us.

111
00:06:24,175 --> 00:06:25,760
I'll find you when I find you.

112
00:06:30,140 --> 00:06:31,975
Guess he really did bail on me.

113
00:06:32,058 --> 00:06:34,436
-You lost, son?
-Oh. Oh, hey.

114
00:06:34,519 --> 00:06:36,646
Please don't kill me
for my cytoplasm.

115
00:06:36,730 --> 00:06:40,901
Oh, child, you've been trapped
in the cycle of violence too long.

116
00:06:40,984 --> 00:06:42,736
I don't know, maybe you're right.

117
00:06:42,819 --> 00:06:44,487
I'm tired of fighting all the time.

118
00:06:44,571 --> 00:06:45,655
Mm-hmm.

119
00:06:45,739 --> 00:06:48,658
I've seen countless souls
waste a billion lifetimes

120
00:06:48,742 --> 00:06:50,118
trying to bust out of here.

121
00:06:50,201 --> 00:06:52,078
But you can't fight the cycle, son.

122
00:06:52,162 --> 00:06:54,831
You got to submit to it.
Serve nature.

123
00:06:54,915 --> 00:06:57,207
Is this where you kill me?

124
00:06:57,292 --> 00:06:59,669
Oh, you are traumatized.

125
00:07:05,800 --> 00:07:09,012
Wow! Pollinating,
building little hexagon houses,

126
00:07:09,095 --> 00:07:10,722
feels good to do something positive.

127
00:07:11,765 --> 00:07:14,309
You see? And I reckon
the warden likes it too.

128
00:07:14,392 --> 00:07:15,685
What are you in for, Morty?

129
00:07:15,769 --> 00:07:19,272
I was a scout for an orc species
looking for planets to conquer.

130
00:07:19,356 --> 00:07:22,984
I was a scout for a sludge species
looking for planets to conquer.

131
00:07:23,068 --> 00:07:27,197
Well, I'm a touch different
because I was a pod person

132
00:07:27,280 --> 00:07:29,240
looking for planets to conquer.

133
00:07:29,324 --> 00:07:31,576
I was helping my grandpa get sap.

134
00:07:31,660 --> 00:07:34,955
I assume it makes energy
or gets you high. I don't know.

135
00:07:35,038 --> 00:07:36,831
Aha. That adds up.

136
00:07:36,915 --> 00:07:40,126
He seems the type
to be locked in here, but you don't.

137
00:07:40,210 --> 00:07:42,504
-Thank you!
-It's a... There's a...

138
00:07:43,672 --> 00:07:46,132
G-O-R...

139
00:07:47,342 --> 00:07:51,304
Should’ve spelled "ape."

140
00:07:52,639 --> 00:07:54,057
On to the next one.

141
00:07:54,140 --> 00:07:56,601
Every cycle evolves
us closer to parole.

142
00:07:56,685 --> 00:07:58,436
-Yeah!
-Yeah!

143
00:07:59,270 --> 00:08:03,024
Oh, I'm so fucking wounded.

144
00:08:03,108 --> 00:08:04,734
Everyone follow my lead.

145
00:08:04,818 --> 00:08:06,236
Your lead? I'm the alpha.

146
00:08:06,319 --> 00:08:07,487
Dog, I'm the alpha.

147
00:08:07,570 --> 00:08:10,407
Easy prey here. Easy pickings.

148
00:08:10,490 --> 00:08:11,491
-Get him.
-Now!

149
00:08:11,574 --> 00:08:13,034
-I'm the alpha.
-On my go!

150
00:08:14,452 --> 00:08:16,413
A hole? This isn't alpha at all.

151
00:08:16,496 --> 00:08:20,000
We're all betas now.
Come on, time to meet the boss.

152
00:08:23,294 --> 00:08:26,423
Hey. I know usually
I'd be trying to eat you and all,

153
00:08:26,506 --> 00:08:28,049
but maybe Los Lobos and The Herd--

154
00:08:28,133 --> 00:08:30,719
Hey! No interspecies solidarity.

155
00:08:35,974 --> 00:08:38,018
The wolves
have been incorporated, sir.

156
00:08:38,101 --> 00:08:39,352
All except for that one.

157
00:08:40,020 --> 00:08:42,480
I'm sorry for those things
I said about apes.

158
00:08:42,563 --> 00:08:44,065
More fermented berry mash.

159
00:08:44,149 --> 00:08:45,191
Right away, sir.

160
00:08:45,275 --> 00:08:47,318
It's time to climb this fucker.

161
00:08:52,323 --> 00:08:53,908
Listen up, pawns.

162
00:08:53,992 --> 00:08:56,369
We begin the task
of scaling this root.

163
00:08:56,453 --> 00:08:59,164
The root will kill you
if you touch it.

164
00:08:59,247 --> 00:09:01,916
You will go one at a time
for observation purposes.

165
00:09:02,000 --> 00:09:03,168
On. Now.

166
00:09:03,251 --> 00:09:05,837
Kind of feel like I'm being punished
for my loyalty, but--

167
00:09:05,920 --> 00:09:07,756
Lead by example, Gorilla Number 3.

168
00:09:23,354 --> 00:09:24,606
Gas 20 feet up.

169
00:09:24,689 --> 00:09:25,690
Next!

170
00:09:37,911 --> 00:09:38,995
You know what? Fine.

171
00:09:39,079 --> 00:09:41,081
If we can't break out, we break him.

172
00:10:18,743 --> 00:10:21,162
So we clean shit from the ocean?

173
00:10:21,246 --> 00:10:22,789
Ocean needs cleanin'.

174
00:10:24,541 --> 00:10:26,751
And we shit in the ocean?

175
00:10:26,835 --> 00:10:28,294
Ocean needs shittin'.

176
00:10:32,215 --> 00:10:35,969
And we shit in the soil
while eating shit out of the soil?

177
00:10:36,052 --> 00:10:38,513
You're pretty hung up
on the shit part of it, aren't you?

178
00:10:43,393 --> 00:10:44,769
What's troubling you, son?

179
00:10:44,853 --> 00:10:47,856
I mean, I like the nonviolence,
don't get me wrong,

180
00:10:47,939 --> 00:10:49,399
and having a shell is fun,

181
00:10:49,482 --> 00:10:52,277
but it just feels like
we're going in circles.

182
00:10:52,360 --> 00:10:54,654
Well, that's what
a healthy ecosystem is.

183
00:10:54,737 --> 00:10:58,324
Eventually, the warden will notice
our piety and set us free.

184
00:10:58,408 --> 00:11:01,286
Until then, we find peace in here.

185
00:11:01,369 --> 00:11:05,582
So a reformed prisoner is someone
who doesn't want to leave the prison?

186
00:11:05,665 --> 00:11:07,167
See? You get it.

187
00:11:07,250 --> 00:11:10,295
Oh, now you're probably
just hungry. Here.

188
00:11:10,378 --> 00:11:12,881
I guess I don't want to eat
whoever that is.

189
00:11:12,964 --> 00:11:14,883
Now, son, that's a vegetable.

190
00:11:14,966 --> 00:11:17,177
No one picks being a vegetable.

191
00:11:17,260 --> 00:11:20,221
You'd have to really give up
to be one of those.

192
00:11:21,306 --> 00:11:24,225
Hey, I think I'm maybe gonna brave

193
00:11:24,309 --> 00:11:25,643
the rest of this life alone.

194
00:11:25,727 --> 00:11:27,812
Well, you know where to find us.

195
00:11:27,896 --> 00:11:29,564
We'll be eating shit.

196
00:13:13,209 --> 00:13:15,461
Sun! Real sun!

197
00:13:17,505 --> 00:13:20,466
Oh, great Warden! I did it!
I figured it out!

198
00:13:20,550 --> 00:13:23,678
The goal is to be a plant, like you!

199
00:13:24,345 --> 00:13:27,140
Whoa! So many nutrients
in the soil up here.

200
00:13:27,223 --> 00:13:28,391
Yes.

201
00:13:28,975 --> 00:13:33,146
The life cycles of the guilty
provide nourishment.

202
00:13:33,229 --> 00:13:34,355
Oh.

203
00:13:34,439 --> 00:13:36,316
But that's more of a by-product

204
00:13:36,399 --> 00:13:38,067
than the point of all this, right?

205
00:13:40,945 --> 00:13:44,907
So... I live up here now?

206
00:13:44,991 --> 00:13:48,244
Oh. This is my spot.

207
00:13:48,328 --> 00:13:51,456
Okay, I can go find my own planet.

208
00:13:53,583 --> 00:13:56,836
You would kinda need to be
a spacefarer for that.

209
00:13:56,919 --> 00:13:58,379
And I don't like those.

210
00:13:58,463 --> 00:14:01,049
But now you know
how cool it is to be a tree.

211
00:14:01,132 --> 00:14:02,550
-Oh.
-Boink!

212
00:14:17,982 --> 00:14:20,651
Okay, we have that
bronze post-mortem in ten,

213
00:14:20,735 --> 00:14:23,529
followed by the all-hands
on opposable thumbs.

214
00:14:29,744 --> 00:14:31,079
I'll reschedule.

215
00:14:33,164 --> 00:14:34,290
Look who it is.

216
00:14:34,374 --> 00:14:35,792
You don't have to do this, man.

217
00:14:35,875 --> 00:14:38,294
The system's rigged.
He wants us fighting each other.

218
00:14:38,378 --> 00:14:40,338
Sounds like I'm on the right side
of history.

219
00:14:40,421 --> 00:14:41,422
Morty!

220
00:14:42,924 --> 00:14:44,300
Alright, Morty, let's shake a leg.

221
00:14:44,384 --> 00:14:46,636
When he respawns in a second,
he's not gonna be any less annoying.

222
00:14:46,719 --> 00:14:48,513
Rick?! Is this a coincidence?

223
00:14:48,596 --> 00:14:50,264
You died at the same time as me?

224
00:14:50,348 --> 00:14:51,474
I saw everything, buddy.

225
00:14:51,557 --> 00:14:53,601
You beat the system,
then the system beat back.

226
00:14:53,684 --> 00:14:54,977
He's evil, Rick!

227
00:14:55,061 --> 00:14:56,771
He's feeding off the cycle of death!

228
00:14:56,854 --> 00:14:59,148
We're all just mulch!

229
00:14:59,232 --> 00:15:01,025
Damn. Pretty diabolical tree.

230
00:15:01,109 --> 00:15:04,028
I don't wanna be mulch!
I wanna go home!

231
00:15:04,112 --> 00:15:06,781
-We have to stop killing each other!
-We will, buddy.

232
00:15:06,864 --> 00:15:08,741
No more death now.
That's what feeds the tree.

233
00:15:08,825 --> 00:15:10,159
I'm back!

234
00:15:11,369 --> 00:15:13,329
After that. Now let's go.

235
00:15:14,622 --> 00:15:19,043
Nants ingonyama bagithi baba!

236
00:15:21,170 --> 00:15:22,213
Thanks for indulging me.

237
00:15:22,296 --> 00:15:25,341
I'm not in the form of a lion,
but I did want to sing the song.

238
00:15:25,425 --> 00:15:26,509
Hello, inmates.

239
00:15:27,760 --> 00:15:29,303
Okay, I deserve that.

240
00:15:29,387 --> 00:15:30,680
But I have something to say.

241
00:15:30,763 --> 00:15:33,266
You expect us to listen to you?!

242
00:15:33,349 --> 00:15:36,352
No, I expect you to listen to Morty.

243
00:15:37,186 --> 00:15:40,398
The Warden seems wise and stoic,
but he's just a big tree.

244
00:15:40,481 --> 00:15:42,275
Which means we can starve him out!

245
00:15:42,358 --> 00:15:44,694
It's a hunger strike! But for him.

246
00:15:44,777 --> 00:15:47,238
We'll all live peacefully
in a contained system.

247
00:15:47,321 --> 00:15:48,364
I don't know.

248
00:15:48,448 --> 00:15:50,408
So instead of escaping,

249
00:15:50,491 --> 00:15:52,743
we'll live in a smaller,
shittier prison?

250
00:15:52,827 --> 00:15:55,371
-I didn't say shittier!
-Gorilla 3, is that you?

251
00:15:55,455 --> 00:15:58,583
It's Hyena 3 now. I got a new job.

252
00:15:58,665 --> 00:15:59,792
Seems like a lateral step.

253
00:15:59,876 --> 00:16:01,711
Think of it more as a biodome.

254
00:16:01,794 --> 00:16:04,130
You've spent a million lifetimes
being dogs and fish.

255
00:16:04,213 --> 00:16:07,508
It won't kill you
to spend one lifetime on this.

256
00:16:07,592 --> 00:16:10,761
Hopefully nothing will kill you.
That's the point of the strike.

257
00:16:11,429 --> 00:16:12,763
You know, he does have a point.

258
00:16:19,020 --> 00:16:20,396
Oh, this was a mistake.

259
00:16:20,480 --> 00:16:22,148
What? This looks great!

260
00:16:22,231 --> 00:16:24,066
Then again, I am a bat.

261
00:16:24,692 --> 00:16:26,486
Welcome to me!

262
00:16:26,569 --> 00:16:28,321
Combined with Morty's
plant-based livin',

263
00:16:28,404 --> 00:16:30,239
we should all age pretty gracefully.

264
00:16:30,323 --> 00:16:31,866
All he needs from you is...

265
00:16:33,242 --> 00:16:35,620
-Hey. Mornin'.
-Shittin' hard or hardly shittin'?

266
00:16:36,621 --> 00:16:38,623
You know, when they pitched me
on this herbivore diet,

267
00:16:38,706 --> 00:16:41,459
I was skeptical,
but then I tried the pizza.

268
00:17:12,531 --> 00:17:14,325
I need 34 bruschettas, all day.

269
00:17:14,407 --> 00:17:15,409
Yes, Chimp!

270
00:17:16,827 --> 00:17:19,038
And you laugh at all my jokes.

271
00:17:19,121 --> 00:17:21,540
It's true, it's true.

272
00:17:21,624 --> 00:17:22,875
I led us all down here

273
00:17:22,959 --> 00:17:25,752
with the express purpose
of killing our tree warden overlord,

274
00:17:25,836 --> 00:17:27,922
which I remind you is still our goal.

275
00:17:28,005 --> 00:17:29,882
He should actually be
pretty weak by now.

276
00:17:29,966 --> 00:17:32,677
However, I knew
we were putting down roots,

277
00:17:32,760 --> 00:17:34,804
but never imagined love would bloom.

278
00:17:34,887 --> 00:17:36,597
What doesn't bloom down here?

279
00:17:39,100 --> 00:17:40,893
Congratulations!

280
00:17:40,977 --> 00:17:43,813
Hyena 3 and Sheep, you may now--

281
00:17:43,896 --> 00:17:46,023
Okay, already doing it. Hot.

282
00:17:49,360 --> 00:17:50,778
Let's party!

283
00:17:59,579 --> 00:18:03,082
I'm so... hungry.

284
00:18:03,165 --> 00:18:06,919
What's happening down there?

285
00:18:09,130 --> 00:18:12,592
Hey! Start killing each other!

286
00:18:12,675 --> 00:18:15,303
Hello? Anybody?

287
00:18:17,054 --> 00:18:20,308
Oh, you little fuckers
are gonna get it now!

288
00:18:32,194 --> 00:18:34,363
"Get bent."

289
00:18:34,447 --> 00:18:37,283
"Get bent"? Little toothless.

290
00:18:37,366 --> 00:18:39,160
-Not that I can beat it.
-Now!

291
00:18:49,295 --> 00:18:51,714
It's working. He's too weak
to get us with his vines!

292
00:18:51,797 --> 00:18:54,634
Good thing too. I didn't anticipate
how old and pacified

293
00:18:54,717 --> 00:18:56,927
our forces would be
by the time this plan worked.

294
00:18:57,011 --> 00:18:59,055
Come on, Hyena 3.
Marriage made you soft.

295
00:18:59,138 --> 00:19:01,766
-Leave him alone!
-You were always a toxic boss!

296
00:19:04,727 --> 00:19:07,188
It's working! Phase 2 now!

297
00:19:19,575 --> 00:19:20,743
Pull!

298
00:19:23,371 --> 00:19:25,331
No! No!

299
00:19:25,414 --> 00:19:28,668
This planet was my retirement!

300
00:19:28,751 --> 00:19:30,294
Say it with me, animals!

301
00:19:30,378 --> 00:19:32,588
Timber!

302
00:19:40,388 --> 00:19:44,392
Doesn't anybody hate anybody anymore?

303
00:19:44,475 --> 00:19:48,437
Hey, birds, don't snakes
always eat your eggs?

304
00:19:48,521 --> 00:19:50,106
Don't... Don't fall for that.

305
00:19:50,189 --> 00:19:53,234
Come on.
Someone's gotta have a grudge.

306
00:19:53,317 --> 00:19:55,361
This is too reformed!

307
00:19:55,444 --> 00:19:57,738
Oh, did we evolve too much?

308
00:19:57,822 --> 00:20:01,617
I actually have
deep respect for spacefarers.

309
00:20:02,243 --> 00:20:04,704
Parked your ships
all nice and neat up there.

310
00:20:07,289 --> 00:20:08,916
If it makes you feel any better,

311
00:20:08,999 --> 00:20:11,836
I didn't steal anything
from the glove boxes!

312
00:20:11,919 --> 00:20:14,296
No! I'm dying!

313
00:20:14,380 --> 00:20:18,175
Plants rule...

314
00:20:24,098 --> 00:20:26,392
So... that's it, then?

315
00:20:26,475 --> 00:20:30,020
I kinda thought we'd be returned
to our original bodies.

316
00:20:30,104 --> 00:20:33,232
No, no, no, no, we will.
We all just gotta believe.

317
00:20:33,315 --> 00:20:35,735
Yeah, we all just gotta
close our eyes.

318
00:20:35,818 --> 00:20:39,238
Hm. Okay. You guys got us this far.

319
00:20:47,747 --> 00:20:49,540
I don't feel anything.
Is it happening?

320
00:20:49,623 --> 00:20:51,250
Oh, it totally is.

321
00:20:51,333 --> 00:20:53,419
You gotta keep
those eyes tight, though.

322
00:20:53,502 --> 00:20:54,754
You sound farther away.

323
00:20:54,837 --> 00:20:58,007
Oh! My leaf became a hand!
It's working!

324
00:20:58,090 --> 00:21:00,426
-Hope that happens to me.
-Whoa! Yeah!

325
00:21:02,011 --> 00:21:05,347
Oh! Oh, so magical.

326
00:21:07,641 --> 00:21:10,478
Interesting how it happened
to them first.

327
00:21:10,561 --> 00:21:11,562
Yeah!

328
00:21:12,229 --> 00:21:13,272
Oh man!

329
00:21:18,235 --> 00:21:19,612
Where have you two been all day?

330
00:21:19,695 --> 00:21:22,031
-Nunya.
-What's that? Biology?

331
00:21:22,114 --> 00:21:24,909
I think I know a thing or two
about that.

332
00:21:27,536 --> 00:21:28,537
Nope.

333
00:22:03,155 --> 00:22:05,449
-Oop. Excuse us.
-Huh.

334
00:22:05,950 --> 00:22:08,118
-Dude!
-That was totally Hyena Number 3.

335
00:22:08,202 --> 00:22:09,328
Guess people got out, huh?

336
00:22:09,411 --> 00:22:11,330
That is not
how I pictured him looking.

337
00:22:12,581 --> 00:22:14,834
-Thanks, hon.
-This might sound crazy,

338
00:22:14,917 --> 00:22:16,961
but do you know
who I think I just saw?

339
00:22:17,044 --> 00:22:19,129
Was it the old man and boy
who saved us from prison

340
00:22:19,213 --> 00:22:21,215
but also left us trapped
in our animal bodies?

341
00:22:21,298 --> 00:22:23,425
You always fucking step
on my stories!

342
00:22:25,010 --> 00:22:26,428
Did you get any of that?

